<title>COLOMBIA: Colombia oil workers threathen indefinite strike.</title>
<headline>Colombia oil workers threathen indefinite strike.</headline>
<dateline>BOGOTA 1996-12-05</dateline>
<text>
<p>Colombia's main oil workers' union will begin an indefinite strike &quot;soon after&quot; an extraordinary meeting Monday, December 9, the union's leader, Hernando Hernandez, said on Thursday.</p>
<p>The strike could extend to workers in private oil companies, including foreign multinationals, following the main USO union's merger with smaller labor organizations in the sector last month.</p>
